{
  "stem": "719.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And like I said, my father invited children to eat with us-- only on special occasions, not during the week, but Sabbath or on a holiday.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I'm just thinking what else to-- from school, I was an average student.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I think I was doing pretty well.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I was pretty bright, because my parents always used to say, you concentrate on education, because during the war, when I really needed to know chores and stuff to survive, I was very clumsy, kind of, because my mother would spoil me.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I was the only one, and she would say, you read a book, you don't have to do things in the house, which was really hard, later on, because I was forced to do things.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Now, one very important moment, if I can go to 1939 already, OK, because summer of 1939, as every summer, I went to my grandma's house.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Actually, my aunt, because my grandma lived with a daughter.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Especially in those days-- which I still think back, it's beautiful-- no parents were put in an old age home, no par-- I don't remember as a child that there were-- there weren't any old age homes, in those days.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I think, if one parent died, the oldest daughter, or whoever could afford it financially, would keep the mother or the father in her place.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this aunt kept her mom, which was my father's mother, my grandma.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I have pictures from-- with my-- from this holiday, from this last holiday.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My grandma was very nice.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was very old-fashioned, and she used to tell me stories from way before First World War, and stuff like that.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I didn't know that something like that was going to happen, later on.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
